# Multi-View Components: Shared UI Checklist

When a page has **multiple return paths** (e.g. early return for form vs list view), shared UI elements must exist in **every path** where they're used.

## The Bug Pattern

```jsx
// ❌ BAD - MediaPreview only in list view; form view has no modal to show
if (isAddPage || isEditPage) {
  return (
    <div>
      <form>
        <ImageUploadField onPreviewClick={openPreview} />  {/* click sets state, but... */}
      </form>
      {/* MediaPreview MISSING - nothing renders! */}
    </div>
  );
}
return (
  <div>
    <DataTable />
    <MediaPreview ... />  {/* Only here */}
  </div>
);
```

## Fix

```jsx
// ✅ GOOD - MediaPreview in BOTH paths
if (isAddPage || isEditPage) {
  return (
    <div>
      <form>...</form>
      <MediaPreview isOpen={...} onClose={...} media={...} />
    </div>
  );
}
return (
  <div>
    <DataTable />
    <MediaPreview ... />
  </div>
);
```

## Senior Dev Checklist

Before marking a feature complete:

1. **Trace the full flow** – If a click/handler opens a modal/preview, verify the modal component is rendered in that view
2. **Audit all return paths** – Any `if (condition) return (...)` must include shared overlays used in that branch
3. **Shared UI elements** – Modals, MediaPreview, ConfirmDialog, Toast containers, etc. must be present wherever their open/trigger logic runs
